article.headline: Yale 69, Dartmouth 64
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Ross Morin scored all 15 of his points in the second half as Yale rallied for a 69-64 win over Dartmouth Friday night. Eric Flato scored a game-high 21 points for the Bulldogs (11-11, 7-2), who have now beaten Dartmouth eight straight times at home. Yale trailed 49-41 before outscoring the Big Green 28-15 in the final 10:24. Morin scored 13 of his points in the decisive stretch. Leon Pattman scored 15 and Alex Barnett had 13 for Dartmouth (8-14, 3-6). The Big Green led by as many as 10 points in the first half and would have taken a double digit advantage to the locker room if not for a Flato 3-pointer in the final minute to make it 38-31. Dartmouth made 16-of-27 shots for 59 percent in the first half.
